{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"agent_message","text":"**Finding**\n\nMilestone 3 does not need a second reload-survivable webview cache for insights. The host already provides the correct reload-recovery mechanism by falling back to the persisted report file, so duplicating that layer in the webview would add complexity without covering a new failure mode.\n\nI updated the active plan to record that decision and narrowed the next slice to a small disclosure fix: make cached/persisted insights state explicit in the UI, in [active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/.claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md#L60). I also wrote the new evolution note at [evolution-2026-04-14-m3-reload-fallback-decision.md](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/.claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-m3-reload-fallback-decision.md#L1).\n\nThis turn did not change code, so I did not run packaging. I synced the updated plan and evolution note to `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`. Next handoff stays narrow: surface when the dashboard is showing cached/persisted insights data."}}
